  • Classes in io.logspace.agent.api.event used by io.logspace.agent.api 
    Class and Description
    Event
    The event is the core part of the logspace domain: they must have a globally unique identifier, they must have a timestamp they can have a type, they can reference other events a global event which is the root cause for other events a parent event which is the direct predecessor event and the can carry any additional information in the form of a collection of key-value pairs.
